=== Enshrined deities ===
; Main deity
: {{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto|Q276944|WD=Q276944|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōkuninushi}}
; Associated deities
: {{ill|WD=Q1502690|lt=Takemikazuchi|Q1502690|WD=Q1502690|WD=Q1502690|lt=Takemikazuchi-no-Mikoto|1=Takemikazuchi}}, {{ill|lt=Kamo Wakeikazuchi-no-Mikoto|Q11634943|WD=Q11634943|lt=Wakeikazuchi-no-Mikoto|1=Kamo-wake-ikazuchi-no-Kami}}

''Shinpen Hitachi no Kuni-shi'' states: "Called Kashima Daimyōjin. According to shrine tradition, there were two enshrined deities: the east was called Nantai-gū, and the west Nyotai-gū, also called Monoimi-gū." In earlier times it was called Kashima Daimyōjin, and there was a paired two-shrine structure of a male-deity shrine and female-deity shrine. The integration of Nyotai-gū is described as "at the beginning of Meiji, the priestly office of the western shrine was dissolved and succeeded by the priest of the eastern shrine"<ref>Hitachi no Kuni-kei Sugiyama Shiki.</ref>, indicating that this occurred in the Meiji period. The present shrine site is considered the continuation of Nantai-gū.

The old site of Nyotai-gū is unknown, but Kisaki Shrine in the precincts enshrines Ōkuninushi's principal consort {{ill|lt=Suseribime|Q8191715|WD=Q8191715|lt=Suseribime-no-Mikoto|1=Suseri-Hime}}. There is also another Kisaki Shrine east of Ōkunitama Shrine (an independent shrine: {{ill|lt=tanritsu|Q7882536|WD=Q7882536|lt=independent shrine|1=Non-denominational}}), but its deity is "Kimi no Gozen," wife of {{ill|lt=Taira no Masakado|Q1207652|WD=Q1207652|1=Taira no Masakado}}, and its {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=shintai|1=UNKNOWN}} is a wooden female figure (Kisaki Shrine sacred image; designated cultural property of Sakuragawa City).

Regarding the deity, one account says: "Perhaps Kashima Ōkami was enshrined; this is also evidenced by 23 songs transmitted at this shrine, all praising the divine power of Kashima deity." It further argues that "Ōkunitama-no-Kami" or "Kuni-gami" was an honorific title for deities who pacified each province, and in Hitachi Province it was another name for Takemikazuchi-no-Mikoto.

=== Precinct shrines ===
* Kisaki Shrine ({{ill|lt=Suseribime|Q8191715|WD=Q8191715|lt=Suseribime-no-Mikoto|1=Suseri-Hime}})
* Yasaka Shrine ({{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|WD=Q272993|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}})
* Aoma Shrine ({{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu-Ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}}, {{ill|WD=Q595520|lt=Tsukuyomi|Q595520|WD=Q595520|WD=Q595520|lt=Tsukuyomi-no-Kami|1=Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto}}, {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Minakanushi|Q2842779|WD=Q2842779|1=Ame-no-Minakanushi}})
* Shichijūgohashira Shrine (collective shrine of the myriad deities; Yaoyorozu no Kami)
