=== Festivals ===
* {{ill|lt=January 3|Q2156|WD=Q2156|1=January 3}}: Kuwe no Matsuri (Kuwauchi Festival) – a {{ill|lt=ta-asobi|Q11577415|WD=Q11577415|1=Ta-asobi}} ritual praying for a good harvest; designated intangible folk cultural property of Sakuragawa City.
* {{ill|lt=January 4|Q2168|WD=Q2168|1=January 4}}: Sayado Meguri Festival – formally called "Ōkunitama Shrine Mass Procession of the Seventy-Five Subsidiary Shrines"; participants carry a large sacred sakaki branch and beat drums while touring subsidiary shrines in the Okunitama district to pray for household safety; designated intangible folk cultural property of Sakuragawa City.
* {{ill|lt=November 15|Q2982|WD=Q2982|1=November 15}}: Annual festival

